"{\"uid\": \"tribuneindia.com-news-parisolympics2024-gold-vi-sada-te-silver-vi-sada-after-neeraj-chopras-mother-arshad-nadeems-mom-echoes-similar-sentiments\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Chandigarh, August 9    Neeraj Chopra and Arshad Nadeed are both Olympic stars of the day.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 90, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As Arshad Nadeed's mother celebrated her son's historic victory, she said: \\\"I prayed for Neeraj Chopra like I prayed for my son.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 183, \"end\": 196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neeraj Chopra\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I see Neeraj the same way as I see my own son.\\\"\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 229, \"end\": 235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gopaldas_Neeraj\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.837289037112183e-14, \"text\": \"Neeraj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gopaldas_Neeraj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gopaldas_Neeraj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If mothers ran the world, there would be no hate, no wars.#ArshadNadeem's mother: 'Neeraj Chopra is like a son to me.\", \"from\": 274, \"to\": 392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 358, \"end\": 371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Neeraj Chopra\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neeraj_Chopra\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I prayed for him too.'\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 415, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"(courtesy indyurdu)#NeerajChopra's mother: 'We are happy with silver.\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 485, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The one who won gold (Arshad Nadeem) is also my child.\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'\\\"\\u2026pic.twitter.com/IWM78tCwpI  - PTI GOJRA (@PTI_Gojra)August 9, 2024    Earlier in the day, Neeraj's mother too had echoed the same sentiments.\", \"from\": 540, \"to\": 684, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 633, \"end\": 639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gopaldas_Neeraj\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.837289037112183e-14, \"text\": \"Neeraj\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gopaldas_Neeraj\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gopaldas_Neeraj\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am happy with the silver, the guy who got gold (Arshad Nadeem) is also my child, everyone goes there after doing a lot of hard work,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In a match, it's about competition, not India and Pakistan.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9841284036126088, \"rank\": 0.015340633832445836, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 887, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999502052, \"rank\": 3.1008785410336185e-11, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We all are preparing to welcome him,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 944, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chopra fell short of retaining his Olympic gold medal, finishing with a best throw of 89.45 metres.\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 1045, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pakistan's Arshad Nadeem won the gold medal by threw an astonishing 92.97 metres for victory.\", \"from\": 1046, \"to\": 1139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1046, \"end\": 1054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999502052, \"rank\": 3.1008785410336185e-11, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Take your experience further with Premium access.Thought-provoking Opinions, Expert Analysis, In-depth Insights and other Member Only Benefits  Already a Member?Sign In Now  The Tribune, now published from Chandigarh, started publication on February 2, 1881, in Lahore (now in Pakistan).\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.123934643796388e-16, \"text\": \"Chandigarh\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chandigarh\"}, {\"begin\": 1403, \"end\": 1409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2090223989905303e-17, \"text\": \"Lahore\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lahore\"}, {\"begin\": 1418, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999502052, \"rank\": 3.1008785410336185e-11, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was started by Sardar Dyal Singh Majithia, a public-spirited philanthropist, and is run by a trust comprising five eminent persons as trustees.The Tribune, the largest selling English daily in North India, publishes news and views without any bias or prejudice of any kind.\", \"from\": 1429, \"to\": 1705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1447, \"end\": 1453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.752196486833372e-25, \"text\": \"Sardar\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sardar\"}, {\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dyal Singh Majithia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dyal_Singh_Majithia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Restraint and moderation, rather than agitational language and partisanship, are the hallmarks of the newspaper.\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1818, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an independent newspaper in the real sense of the term.The Tribune has two sister publications, Punjabi Tribune (in Punjabi) and Dainik Tribune (in Hindi).\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1921, \"end\": 1936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punjabi Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_Tribune\"}, {\"begin\": 1941, \"end\": 1948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\", \"score\": 0.999995597294543, \"rank\": 4.398862052705292e-06, \"text\": \"Punjabi\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punjabi_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1954, \"end\": 1968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dainik_Tribune\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dainik Tribune\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/